"Wallbaum H., Ostermeyer Y., Gotob Y.","User- and Climate-tailored Design - A vision and chance for global acceptance of sustainable building solutions [Nutzer- und klimaangepasstes Bauen - Leitbild und Chance für die globale Verbreitung von nachhaltigen Gebäudelösungen]",2011,"Bautechnik","88","1",,"3","16",,,10.1002/bate.201110001,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-78651107658&partnerID=40&md5=95d0a66b024cd9fe4469fcd5b5f7549d","ETH Zürich, Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich, Wolfgang-Pauli-Strasse 15, CH-8093 Zurich, Switzerland; EMPA, Swiss Federal Laboratories for Materials Science and Technology, CH-8600 Duebendorf, Switzerland","Wallbaum, H., ETH Zürich, Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich, Wolfgang-Pauli-Strasse 15, CH-8093 Zurich, Switzerland; Ostermeyer, Y., ETH Zürich, Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich, Wolfgang-Pauli-Strasse 15, CH-8093 Zurich, Switzerland; Gotob, Y., EMPA, Swiss Federal Laboratories for Materials Science and Technology, CH-8600 Duebendorf, Switzerland","The paper gives an overview on background and outlook on sustainable development as a trend and vision in the building sector. Focus is on the necessity to adapt existing experience values and concepts in when transferring them to other climate zones and cultures than they originate from. This approach shows a great potential in regards to a solution of problems like global warming and limited resources. Experiences with analyzed projects show however, that, despite the goal to create working and healthy homes, technologies and concepts often are not tailored to local conditions. Using the example of a cooperation project of the Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zürich (ETH Zürich) and the Swiss Federal Laboratories for Materials Science and Technology (EMPA) in which a climate adapted building envelope was developed the paper shows what modifications have to be made. This is especially relevant in the field of building physics in order to increase efficiency and avoid damages to the building and inhabitants and create sustainable homes. Besides this the interchange of the developed envelope, associated production methods and other relevant frame conditions, like local resource availability, is used to demonstrate what barriers and potential synergies can emerge in the course of such a project. © 2011 Ernst & Sohn Verlag für Architektur und technische Wissenschaften GmbH & Co. KG, Berlin.","Climate-adaptation; comfort; hygrothermal simulation; inner room climate; Japan; resource efficiency; socio-cultural Aspects; subtropical climate; sustainable construction; Sustainable development",,,,,,,"Meadows, D., (1969) Die Grenzen des Wachstums - Der Bericht des Club of Rome Zur Lage der Menschheit; Bringezu, S., Bleischwitz, R., (2009) Sustainable Resource Management, , Germany; Deklaration des World Resources Forum 2009, , http://www.worldresourcesforum.org/wrf_declaration, online unter 17.11.2010; Mineral Commodity Summaries 2008, , USGS; F.A.Z., 10.07.2007, Nr. 157 / Seite T1Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (2007): IPCC Fourth Assessment Report; World Energy Outlook 2010, , International Energy Agency 2009 (IEA); Internationale Energie Agentur, , www.IEA.org, online unter 17.11.2010; (2010) Global economic Prospects 2010: Crisis, Finance and Growth, , World Bank, SKU: 18226; Eurostat-Daten DCM, , http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/statistics_explained/index.php/ Domestic_material_consumption_%28DMC%, online unter:; Eurostat Daten TMR, , http://epp.eurostat.ec.europa.eu/portal/page/portal/ environmental_accounts/data/main_tables, online unter:; (2008) Measuring Material Flows and Resource Productivity, p. 94. , Volume I., The OECD Guide; Sachs, W., Santarius, T., (2005) Fair Future - Begrenzte Ressourcen und Globale Gerechtigkeit. München: Verlag C. H. Beck; Brown, D., Dillard, J., Marshall, R.S., (2006) Triple Bottom Line: A Business Metaphor for A Social Construct; www.DGNB.de, Deutsche Gesellsc